<paragraph id="8B9D91563C395B23FF4DFEC8FE8BFE12" blockId="9.[192,802,199,498]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">LEGS: The femur and patella bear only several solitary hairs and bristles. The tibiae of the first to third legs bear several spines and bristles, namely on the outer side. Tarsomere I of the first to third legs bears bristlecombs composed of approximately 9–13 bristles. The inner sides of all legs bear one or two rows of spines. The fourth legs lack bristlecombs and bear only sparse, short spines.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9D91563C395B23FF4DFDD4FEB0FCA3" blockId="9.[192,802,536,835]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
